How to Patch cTCE to NWChem-6.0
===============================

1.  Download NWChem-6.0 source code. (http://www.nwchem-sw.org/images/Nwchem-6.0.tar.gz)
    scp NWChem-6.0.tar.gz [username]@chinook.emsl.pnl.gov:/home/[username]/
    scp ctce-b1.0.zip [username]@chinook.emsl.pnl.gov:/home/[username]/
    login to Chinook
    tar -zxvf Nwchem-6.0.tar.gz
    mv /home/[username]/nwchem-6.0/ /home/[username]/nwchem-6.0-ctce/

2.  Copy and unzip cTCE source code. (ctce-b1.0.zip)
    mv ctce-b1.0.zip /home/[username]/nwchem-6.0-ctce/
    cd /home/[username]/nwchem-6.0-ctce/
    unzip ctce-b1.0.zip

3.  Normal NWChem compilation.
    cd /home/[username]/nwchem-6.0-ctce/ctce/
    module purge
    module load nwchem
    ./compile_nw6.sh

4.  Patch cTCE and compile.
    ./patch.sh
    ./compile.sh

5.  Test case can be found in /ctce/testfile


Troubleshooting
===============

1.  Make sure NWCHEM_TOP path is set properly. (compile.sh)
2.  Make sure 'module purge' and 'module load nwchem' on Chinook for proper environmental setting.
3.  Make sure ctce folder is in '/nwchem-6.0-ctce/ctce/', not '/nwchem-6.0-ctce/src/ctce/'.
4.  Email Pai-Wei Lai (paiwei.lai@gmail.com) for more help.

